author: thedakaboom
content:
This edgy music-driven comedy duo combines the musical genres of pop, hip-hop, opera, jazz, musical theatre, electronica and a cappella to modernize and reinvent the vaudeville artform.

Ben McLain has made appearances on General Hospital, though he spends most of his time recording and touring with electronic vocal band Sonos, featured on the final season of NBC's The Sing Off. www.sonosings.com

Actor/musician Paul Peglar works extensively with internet stars Chester See and Lana McKissack, was the original piano player on the first season of Fox's Glee and recently shot a Comedy Central pilot with sketch trio Good Neighbor. www.paulpeglar.com

Last year Dakaboom embarked on an east coast tour in promotion of their debut album release "Get Awesome". 2013 has them embarking on a six-month tour throughout the US, hosting the Los Angeles A Cappella Festival at USC and releasing their DVD: Live in Los Angeles.
title: thedakaboom

author: Justin James Hughes
content:
Justin James Hughes is a winner. Where others quit, Justin perseveres. Where others break, Justin gets stronger. Where others stop to take a break, well, Justin stops too but only to laugh at how silly "breaks" are. He doesn't know defeat, only success. He doesn't know "can't", only "can". He doesn't know where Sri Lanka is on a map... but let's face it, who does? Justin is the epitome of all that is right and glorious in this world! He also likes animals, short walks on the beach, and board games. He has been known to make stuff up and his words are steeped in sarcasm and must never be taken seriously. Ever. Even this very paragraph is filled with lies and half-truths. Thusly, watch his videos with a grain of salt... or perhaps two grains of rice and one teaspoon soysauce as it is salty in itself.

Currently Fiesta Movement Agent. http://disclosur.es/tJYmv2
title: Justin James Hughes
